robert pozen  wikipedia robert pozen from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search robert pozen born robert charles pozen  august   age  bridgeport ct usa nationality  united states alma mater harvard college yale law school robert charles pozen born  is an american financial executive with a strong interest in public policy he is the former chairman of mfs investment management the oldest mutual fund company in the united states he is also a senior lecturer at harvard business school and a senior fellow at the brookings institution contents  education and family  investment industry career  teaching positions  public service  boardsmemberships  key publications  selected books  selected financial articles  external links  references education and familyedit pozen grew up in bridgeport connecticut where he attended public high school and won a scholarship to attend harvard college in  he graduated summa cum laude and phi beta kappa from harvard which awarded him a knox traveling fellowship in  pozen received a law degree from yale law school where he served on the editorial board of the yale law journal he received a jsd from yale in  for his doctoral thesis on state enterprises in africa he is a member of the massachusetts new york and washington dc bars he has been married for more than  years to elizabeth kelner pozen a psychotherapist and figurative painter they live in boston massachusetts and have two adult children joanna and david investment industry careeredit pozen was an executive at fidelity investments from  to  eventually rising to vice chairman of the company and president of fmr co the investment adviser to fidelity’s mutual funds in the latter role he had oversight of fidelity’s global portfolio management and research teams during his tenure as president fidelity’s assets under management increased from  billion to  billion he also was a director of fidelity’s insurance company and credit card bank pozen became chairman of mfs investment management in february  in that position he advised the firm on strategic initiatives and longterm planning speaking on corporate governance he has been credited with enhancing the organization’s legal audit and risk functions he retired as chairman in july  and is now chairman emeritus he continues to serve as a member of the mfs mutual fund boards in  he was recognized for his work in the mutual fund industry with the fund action lifetime achievement award teaching positionsedit  visiting professor georgetown university law center  associate professor new york university law school  john olin visiting professor harvard law school  senior lecturer mit sloan school of management –present senior lecturer harvard business school –present mit sloan school of management public serviceedit in addition to his private sector and teaching posts pozen has dedicated time during his career to public service he was associate general counsel for the us securities and exchange commission sec from  to  in  and  he served as a member of president george w bushs commission to strengthen social security his proposal for utilizing a progressive indexing methodology to address social security’s longterm solvency issue received national attention including a mention during president bushs  state of the union address at the state level pozen served as secretary of economic affairs in  under thenmassachusetts governor mitt romney pozen was responsible for all economicrelated areas including banking consumer affairs insurance and labor in  pozen served as chairman of the secs committee to improve financial reporting working with both private and public sector experts the committee made several actionable recommendations to improve the us financial reporting system many of which have been implemented boardsmembershipsedit board member medtronic inc board member the nielsen company former board member bell canada enterprises trustee commonwealth fund healthcare foundation board member harvard neurodiscovery center former board member national basketball hall of fame former vice chairman boston public library foundation fellow american academy of arts and sciences senior fellow brookings institution member council on foreign relations member committee on capital markets regulation key publicationsedit selected booksedit the fund industry how your money is managed with theresa hamacher  john wiley too big to save how to fix the us financial system  john wiley financial institutions investment management  west publishing selected financial articlesedit financial times shortselling bans are a mistake august   science translational medicine defining success for translational research organizations with heather kline august   huffington post social security reform is the key to the debt ceiling debate july   washington post a debt plan republicans can support july   washington post wading into moneymarket funds with theresa hamacher july   financial times dont hobble money market funds with theresa hamacher june   harvard business review managing yourself extreme productivity may  financial times european funds are outgunning us rivals with theresa hamacher april   washington post a bond backfire after racing to buy longterm treasuries and sell taxexempt funds with theresa hamacher april   morningstar advisor the global fundleadership playoffs europe vs the us with theresa hamacher aprilmay  forbes heretic reality mortgage interest deduction needs to be slashed march   washington post why liberals should back social security reform march   financial times japan can rebuild on new economic foundations march   wall street journal a new model for corporate boards december   harvard business review the case for professional boards december  new york times for social security a birthday makeover august   wall street journal bashing beijing will not help our trade deficit august   wall street journal  is plenty for deposit insurance june   financial times chatter about a new global currency is overblown july   forbes stop pining for glasssteagall septemberoctober  wall street journal systemic risk and the fed july   wall street journal how to value toxic bank assets february   financial times foundations to be laid before bridging gap november   new york times think first bail out later june   new york times reporting for duty march   harvard business review if private equity sized up your business november  fortune china goes from red to gray june   harvard business review before you split that ceo chair april  pensions  investments overstating performance february   usa today why my plan to fix social security will work june   foreign affairs mind the gap vol  no   marchapril  the economist the route to real pension reform  january   harvard business review arm yourself for the coming battle over social security vol  at  november  harvard business review institutional investors the reluctant activists vol  of  januaryfebruary  external linksedit harvard business school faculty home page bob pozen site linkedin facebook twitter referencesedit jason furman march   an analysis of using progressive indexing to set social security benefits center on budget and policy priorities  bloomberg news march   bush hawks financier pozens plan as social security compromise  the new republic april   ryan lizza face plant the progress report may   pozen blasts bush privatization plans  reuters may   mark felsenthal drop private accounts  us social security advisor barrons july   jack willoughby a prudent man to the rescue v t e cabinet of governor mitt romney – lieutenant governor kerry healey – secretary of health and human services ron preston – timothy r murphy – secretary of environmental affairs ellen roy herzfelder – stephen pritchard – robert w golledge jr – secretary of public safety  homeland security edward a flynn – robert c haas – secretary of transportation daniel grabauskas – john cogliano – secretary of administration and finance eric kriss – thomas trimarco – secretary of economic development robert pozen – ranch c kimball – secretary of elder affairs jennifer davis carey – secretary of veterans services thomas g kelley – secretary of commonwealth development douglas i foy – andrew gottlieb – secretary of workforce development jane edmonds – v t e bce inc corporate directors george a cope ceo andré bérard anthony s fell ed lumley john h mcarthur jim pattison michael sabia paul tellier richard currie robert pozen fixedline telecommunications bell aliant atlantic canada bell canada urban on  qc bell internet isp bell mts mb northerntel northern on northwestel northern canada ontera northern on télébec rural qc dmts dryden ontario area mobile telecommunications bell mobility bell mts mb inukshuk wireless northerntel mobility northwestel including latitude wireless pc mobile prepaid solo mobile télébec mobilité virgin mobile canada television services bell fibe tv iptv – urban on  qc bell mobile tv mobile iptv bell tv satellite cablevision northern qc fibreop iptv – bell aliant regions mts tv iptv – mb other properties bell media  maple leaf sports  entertainment  montreal canadiens  the source glentel  advertising and sponsorships bell centre bell mts place place bell frank and gordon kids help phone solo mobile  eckored tour tiff bell lightbox related att corporation nortel society of composers authors and music publishers of canada v bell canada telesat canada an additional  interest is held by the bce master trust fund bells pension plan authority control worldcat identities viaf  isni     sudoc  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlerobertpozenoldid categories  birthsliving peoplesocial security united statesharvard business school facultygeorgetown university facultystate cabinet secretaries of massachusettsmit sloan school of management facultyamerican jewsharvard university alumniphi beta kappa membershidden categories pages using infobox person with unknown param