tor of fidelity’s insurance company and credit card bank pozen became chairman of mfs investment management in february  in that position he advised the firm on strategic initiatives and longterm planning speaking on corporate governance he has been credited with enhancing the organization’s legal audit and risk functions he retired as chairman in july  and is now chairman emeritus he continues to serve as a member of the mfs mutual fund boards in  he was recognized for his work in the mutual fund industry with the fund action lifetime achievement award teaching positionsedit  visiting professor georgetown university law center  associate professor new york university law school  john olin visiting professor harvard law school  senior lecturer mit sloan school of management –present senior lecturer harvard business school –present mit sloan school of management public serviceedit in addition to his private sector and teaching posts pozen has dedicated time during his career to public service he was associate general counsel for the us securities and exchange commission sec from  to  in  and  he served as a member of president george w bushs commission to strengthen social security his proposal for utilizing a progressive indexing methodology to address social security’s longterm solvency issue received national attention including a mention during president bushs  state of the union address at the state level pozen served as secretary of economic affairs in  under thenmassachusetts governor mitt romney pozen was responsible for all economicrelated areas including banking consumer affairs insurance and labor in  pozen served as chairman of the secs committee to improve financial reporting working with both private and public sector experts the committee made several actionable recommendations to improve the us financial reporting system many of which have been implemented boardsmembershipsedit board member medtronic inc board member the nielsen company former board m