d won a scholarship to attend harvard college in  he graduated summa cum laude and phi beta kappa from harvard which awarded him a knox traveling fellowship in  pozen received a law degree from yale law school where he served on the editorial board of the yale law journal he received a jsd from yale in  for his doctoral thesis on state enterprises in africa he is a member of the massachusetts new york and washington dc bars he has been married for more than  years to elizabeth kelner pozen a psychotherapist and figurative painter they live in boston massachusetts and have two adult children joanna and david investment industry careeredit pozen was an executive at fidelity investments from  to  eventually rising to vice chairman of the company and president of fmr co the investment adviser to fidelity’s mutual funds in the latter role he had oversight of fidelity’s global portfolio management and research teams during his tenure as president fidelity’s assets under management increased from  billion to  billion he also was a director of fidelity’s insurance company and credit card bank pozen became chairman of mfs investment management in february  in that position he advised the firm on strategic initiatives and longterm planning speaking on corporate governance he has been credited with enhancing the organization’s legal audit and risk functions he retired as chairman in july  and is now chairman emeritus he continues to serve as a member of the mfs mutual fund boards in  he was recognized for his work in the mutual fund industry with the fund action lifetime achievement award teaching positionsedit  visiting professor georgetown university law center  associate professor new york university law school  john olin visiting professor harvard law school  senior lecturer mit sloan school of management –present senior lecturer harvard business school –present mit sloan school of management public serviceedit in addition to his private sector and teaching posts pozen has dedicated time during his career to public service he was associate general counsel for the us securities and exchange commission sec from  to  in  and  he served as a member of president george w bushs commission to strengthen social security his proposal for utilizing a progressive indexing methodology to address social security’s longterm solvency issue received national attention including a mention during president bushs  state of the union address at the state level pozen served as secretary of economic affairs in  under thenmassachusetts governor mitt romney pozen was responsible for all economicrelated areas including banking consumer affairs insurance and labor in  pozen served as chairman of the secs committee to improve financial reporting working with both private and public sector experts the committee made several actionable recommendations to improve the us financial reporting system many of which have been implemented boardsmembershipsedit board member medtronic inc board member the nielsen company former board member bell canada enterprises trustee commonwealth fund healthcare foundation board member harvard neurodiscovery center former board member national basketball hall of fame former vice chairman boston public library foundation fellow american academy of arts and sciences senior fellow brookings institution member council on foreign relations member committee on capital markets regulation key publicationsedit selected booksedit the fund industry how your money is managed with theresa hamacher  john wiley too big to save how to fix the us financial system  john wiley financial institutions investment management  west publishing selected financial articlesedit financial times shortselling bans are a mistake august   science translational medicine defining success for translational research organizations with heather kline august   huffington post social security reform is the key to the debt ceiling debate july   washington post a debt plan re