sloan school of management he is also a senior fellow at the brookings institution he has extensive experience in business government and journalism bob was executive chairman of mfs investment management from  to  during this period the assets of mfs more than doubled from a starting point of  billionfrom  through  he served in various positions at fidelity investment during his tenure as president of fidelity management and research from  thru  the assets of the fidelity funds rose from  billlion to  billion bob served as associate general counsel of the sec in the late s and chairman of the secs advisory committee on financial reporting in  he was a member of the presidents commission to strengthen social security and served as secretary of economic affairs under massachusetts governor mitt romneybob has taught at georgetown and nyu as well as harvard and mit he has published seven books mainly on financial issues his latest book extreme productivity boost your results reduce your hours was  on fast company’s list of best business books for  in addition he often writes editorials for the financial times the washington post and the wall street journalbob is an outside director of medtronic nielsen and amc a secondtier subsidiary of the world bank he is also on the governing board of several nonprofit organizations he received the  fund action lifetime achievement award for his work in the mutual fund industrybob graduated summa cum laude from harvard college and obtained a law degree from yale law school where he was a member of the editorial board of the yale law journal he also received a doctorate from yale law school for a book he wrote on state enterprises in africa faculty media innovationwork blog timemaximizing strategies of highly successful people even the most successful individuals are looking for new and better ways to get more accomplished while maintaining or increasing their quality of life view innovationwork blog productivity wisdom bob pozens top five articles regardless of location industry or occupation productivity is a challenge faced by every professional following us throughout our respective careers even as a professor and published author on view how to train your brain to push past perfectionism perfectionism isnt hardwired its learned which means we can unlearn it too with these methods view in pursuit of profession being extremely productive ever want to be more productive but don’t know how to get started i talked to author robert pozen senior lecturer at mit sloan school of management about how his book extreme productivity can view surprisingly simple ways to get more done in less time become a productivity pro with these clever ideas to maximize your workday—and your job search view  habits of the most productive people you know those superproductive people who manage to get more done than the rest of us these are their secrets view state programs to solve the uss retirement crisis the us is facing a retirement crisis about one third of americans have no retirement savings and most dont have enough savings to retire comfortably view productivity hacks from an mit efficiency expert between endless email chains office chatter and meetings to discuss future meetings it can be hard to get work done some days but it doesn’t have to be that way view listen the work day is getting longer mit sloan professor bob pozen joins a bbc panel discussing how the advancement in technology make it harder to leave your work at the office view how obamacare inadvertently threatens the financial health of small businesses and what states should do about it obamacare includes a myriad of regulatory incentives and exemptions that define the parameters of the employer mandate however these have inadvertent consequences view contact information office e phone   fax   email bobpozenmitedu website support staff name sumaiya rahman phone  email sumaiyarmitedu teaches in maximizing your personal productivity how to beco